Rust has full support for linking object files with a C calling convention. Similarly, you can export Rust functions and call them from C. You can do it by hand if you want: extern "C" { fn abs(x: i32) -> i32;
} fn main() { let x = -42; let abs_x = unsafe { abs(x) }; println!("{x}, {abs_x}");
} We already saw this in the Safe FFI Wrapper exercise . This assumes full knowledge of the target platform. Not recommended for production. We will look at better options next.

